I"Íh<img src="/assets/Waveform/Good/BigMeters.png" alt="Big Meters">
<div class="image-caption">Big Meters</div>

<p>Your favorite part of the week has arrived! Part 7 day!</p>

<p>As I‚Äôm slowly becoming more familiar with Waveform, you may notice that the review is also becoming more focused. Today I‚Äôm going to cover the good, the bad and the weird of recording in Waveform 9. Recording Audio and MIDI are the topics.</p>

<p>You may notice that this article is perhaps more substantive than others, and that‚Äôs because this is what I do day in and day out. I record. I still put in a lot of effort to other sections, but this topic comes more naturally to me due to how I‚Äôve been using Waveform this last month and my general life experience.</p>

<p>This article has some of my favorite features in the software, and some things that other DAWs really should learn from, but like with all software there‚Äôs some small things that sour the experience a bit more than it seems like they should. Regardless, Waveform excels in this area‚Ä¶ mostly.</p>

